abstract: A  man suspected to be homeless intentionally broke windows at local government buildings in Mississippi so he could spend the night in jail to shelter from the cold, a county sheriff said.
snippet: A  man suspected to be homeless intentionally broke windows at local government buildings in Mississippi so he could spend the night in jail to shelter from the cold, a county sheriff said.
lead_paragraph: NATCHEZ, Miss. — A man suspected to be homeless intentionally broke windows at local government buildings in Mississippi so he could spend the night in jail to shelter from the cold, a county sheriff said.
headline_main: Sheriff: Man Committed Crime So He Could Be Housed in Jail
headline_print_headline: Sheriff: Man Committed Crime So He Could Be Housed in Jail

abstract: A Virginia woman has been convicted of child neglect in the death of her 4-year-old son who shot himself in the head last year.
snippet: A Virginia woman has been convicted of child neglect in the death of her 4-year-old son who shot himself in the head last year.
lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — A Virginia woman has been convicted of child neglect in the death of her 4-year-old son who shot himself in the head last year.
headline_main: Mom Convicted in Death of 4-Year-Old Who Shot Himself
headline_print_headline: Mom Convicted in Death of 4-Year-Old Who Shot Himself

abstract: Croatia is holding a tight presidential election this weekend that is seen as a test for the conservative government only days before the European Union’s newest member state takes over the bloc's presidency for the first time.
snippet: Croatia is holding a tight presidential election this weekend that is seen as a test for the conservative government only days before the European Union’s newest member state takes over the bloc's presidency for the first time.
lead_paragraph: ZAGREB, Croatia — Croatia is holding a tight presidential election this weekend that is seen as a test for the conservative government only days before the European Union’s newest member state takes over the bloc's presidency for the first time.
headline_main: Croatia Holds Tight Presidential Vote Before EU Chairmanship
headline_print_headline: Croatia Holds Tight Presidential Vote Before EU Chairmanship

abstract: Students of New Delhi's Jamia Millia Islamia University have turned the campus' sandstone walls into a canvas of discontent.

abstract: As Hassan Rouhani meets with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, there was speculation that he hoped to convey a message to President Trump.
snippet: As Hassan Rouhani meets with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, there was speculation that he hoped to convey a message to President Trump.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — President Hassan Rouhani of Iran met on Friday with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan, as speculation intensified that Mr. Abe’s friendly relations with the Iranians and the Trump administration could create a new diplomatic opening to ease tensions.

abstract: Andrew Bailey, head of Britain’s financial watchdog, will be the next governor of the Bank of England, where his top challenge will be navigating any choppy waters during the country's departure from the European Union.
snippet: Andrew Bailey, head of Britain’s financial watchdog, will be the next governor of the Bank of England, where his top challenge will be navigating any choppy waters during the country's departure from the European Union.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Andrew Bailey, head of Britain’s financial watchdog, will be the next governor of the Bank of England, where his top challenge will be navigating any choppy waters during the country's departure from the European Union.
headline_main: Andrew Bailey to Succeed Carney as Bank of England Governor
headline_print_headline: Andrew Bailey to Succeed Carney as Bank of England Governor

abstract: Andrew Bailey, the head of a financial regulator, will take over the role from Mark Carney.
snippet: Andrew Bailey, the head of a financial regulator, will take over the role from Mark Carney.
lead_paragraph: The British government on Friday named Andrew Bailey, the head of the Financial Conduct Authority, to be the next chief of the Bank of England. Mr. Bailey, who worked at the central bank for over 30 years before leaving to run the financial watchdog in 2016, will succeed Mark Carney.

abstract: Former Malaysian Prime Minister Najib Razak made a religious oath in a mosque Friday denying a new accusation that he ordered the killing of a Mongolian woman 13 years ago.

lead_paragraph: KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia — Former Malaysian Prime Minister Najib Razak made a religious oath in a mosque Friday denying a new accusation that he ordered the killing of a Mongolian woman 13 years ago.
headline_main: Malaysian Ex-PM Takes Islamic Oath Denying Murder Claim

abstract: The death toll in the shooting outside the Moscow headquarters of Russia's main security agency has risen to two, officials said Friday as investigators pressed to uncover the assailant's motives.
